---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="About"
  description="Career timeline, education, certifications, and languages."
  pathname="/about"
>
  <article class="container-prose pt-20 pb-16">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold mb-6" style="line-height: 1.2;">About</h1>
      <blockquote class="text-lg mb-6">
        "I build the physical foundations that empower logical intelligence."
      </blockquote>
      <p style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
        Infrastructure Expert bridging the gap between Hardware Depth and AI Intelligence. I
        started in network infrastructure, moved through endpoint and IT support, then VMware
        virtualization, and now I build AI-native developer tooling for cross-border e-commerce
        support. Three languages, four roles, one consistent thread — taking ownership of the
        layer beneath the surface so the layer above can run cleanly.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Experience</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3 mb-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold m-0">Global-e — Technical Support Engineer</h3>
          <span class="text-xs whitespace-nowrap" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
            Dec 2025 – Present
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
          Seoul, South Korea (Hybrid) · Application / SQL / Tech Support Team
        </div>
        <ul class="text-sm list-disc list-inside space-y-1" style="color: var(--fg);">
          <li>End-to-end merchant technical support with full case ownership and precise issue analysis</li>
          <li>Root cause analysis through application logs, SQL diagnostics, and debugging tools</li>
          <li>Cross-functional escalation coordination across global time zones</li>
          <li>Concurrent case management prioritized by impact, urgency, and key cross-team dependencies</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3"><a href="/projects/global-e">See sanctuary project →</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3 mb-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold m-0">PuzzleSystems — VMware Engineer</h3>
          <span class="text-xs whitespace-nowrap" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
            Jun 2025 – Nov 2025
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
          Yeongdeungpo District, Seoul · Virtualization / VMware / Cloud Platform Team
        </div>
        <ul class="text-sm list-disc list-inside space-y-1" style="color: var(--fg);">
          <li>Periodic inspections and vulnerability assessments across VMware environments</li>
          <li>Remote and on-site technical support for NSX-based network virtualization</li>
          <li>Windows 11 VDI migration deployment for enterprise clients</li>
          <li>IDC network reliability and security improvement</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3"><a href="/projects/puzzle">See GPU VDI Benchmark project →</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3 mb-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold m-0">Toss Insurance — IT Supporter</h3>
          <span class="text-xs whitespace-nowrap" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
            Jan 2025 – May 2025
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
          Guro District, Seoul · Internal System / Operation / System Platform Team
        </div>
        <ul class="text-sm list-disc list-inside space-y-1" style="color: var(--fg);">
          <li>Windows / macOS environment support; Microsoft 365 user lifecycle and licensing</li>
          <li>IP exhaustion and subnet misconfiguration diagnostics affecting Wi-Fi</li>
          <li>Google Workspace 2FA and security access exception management</li>
          <li>Malware detection accuracy validation, reducing false positives</li>
          <li>Python + Slack Bot security solution provisioning automation</li>
          <li>Hypervisor-based isolated environments for public-institution software conflicts</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3"><a href="/projects/toss">See Slack Bot automation project →</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-4">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3 mb-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold m-0">Ubiquoss — Network Engineer</h3>
          <span class="text-xs whitespace-nowrap" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
            Feb 2023 – Apr 2024
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
          Seongnam, Gyeonggi · Network / Architect / Overseas Tech Team
        </div>
        <ul class="text-sm list-disc list-inside space-y-1" style="color: var(--fg);">
          <li>Network architecture design and simulation environments for system stability</li>
          <li>Redundant monitoring and failover paths for data center traffic reliability</li>
          <li>Ultra-low-latency / high-bandwidth tuning + L4 load balancing</li>
          <li>L3 switch OS validation for defect detection and stability</li>
          <li>Real-time technical support for customers in Korea, Japan, and the U.S.</li>
          <li>CIDR-based subnetting for department / floor segmentation and access control</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mt-3"><a href="/projects/ubiquoss">See Private 5G project →</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Education</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>
          <strong>Academic Credit Bank System</strong> — Bachelor's degree, Computer Science
          <span style="color: var(--fg-soft);">(Jan 2021 – Aug 2024)</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cisco Networking Academy</strong> — Certificate Program, System / Networking /
          LAN/WAN Management
          <span style="color: var(--fg-soft);">(2021 – 2022)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Certifications</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><strong>HashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate (003)</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Network Administrator II</strong> (네트워크관리사 2급) — KAIT</li>
        <li><strong>JLPT N1</strong> — Japanese Language Proficiency Test</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Languages</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><strong>Korean</strong> — Native</li>
        <li><strong>English</strong> — Professional working proficiency</li>
        <li><strong>Japanese</strong> — Professional working proficiency (JLPT N1)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Skills</h2>
      <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--fg);">
        Linux, Windows, macOS · Python, TypeScript, SQL, Bash, PowerShell · Network (L2/L3, 5G
        RAN/Core, SNMP, TCP/IP) · Security · Virtualization (VMware vSphere / NSX) · Automation
        · Technical Support · IaC (Terraform) · MCP (Model Context Protocol) · Coralogix ·
        MSSQL · Snowflake · Atlassian (JIRA / Confluence) · Zendesk · Microsoft 365
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--fg-soft);">
        Open to conversations — see <a href="/contact">Contact</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
